adGenAOSMuxID.name: adGenAOSMuxID
adGenAOSMuxID.contactinfo: Technical Support Dept. Postal: ADTRAN, Inc. 901 Explorer Blvd. Huntsville, AL 35806 Tel: +1 800 726-8663 Fax: +1 256 963 6217 E-mail: support@adtran.com
adGenAOSMuxID.description: The MIB module for the management of AOS products with TDM multiplexing and/or cross-connects.

adGenAOSXConnectEntry.name: adGenAOSXConnectEntry
adGenAOSXConnectEntry.description: An entry in the Cross-Connect Configuration Table

adGenAOSXConnectIndex.name: adGenAOSXConnectIndex
adGenAOSXConnectIndex.description: A number that uniquely defines the cross-connect

adGenAOSXConnectFirstIfType.name: adGenAOSXConnectFirstIfType
adGenAOSXConnectFirstIfType.description: The type of interface from which a cross-connect is being made

adGenAOSXConnectFirstIfNumber.name: adGenAOSXConnectFirstIfNumber
adGenAOSXConnectFirstIfNumber.description: A number that defines the interface described by adGenAOSXConnectFirstIfType -- set to 0 if the interface can be defined by adGenAOSXConnectFirstIfSlot and adGenAOSXConnectFirstIfPort

adGenAOSXConnectFirstSubIfNumber.name: adGenAOSXConnectFirstSubIfNumber
adGenAOSXConnectFirstSubIfNumber.description: A number that further defines some interfaces -- set to 0 if the interface can be defined by adGenAOSXConnectFirstIfSlot and adGenAOSXConnectFirstIfPort

adGenAOSXConnectFirstIfSlot.name: adGenAOSXConnectFirstIfSlot
adGenAOSXConnectFirstIfSlot.description: The slot number containing the interface described by adGenAOSXConnectFirstIfType -- set to 0 if the interface can be defined by adGenAOSXConnectFirstIfNumber (and adGenAOSXConnectFirstSubIfNumber) Note: 0 is also a valid slot number.

adGenAOSXConnectFirstIfPort.name: adGenAOSXConnectFirstIfPort
adGenAOSXConnectFirstIfPort.description: The port number of the interface described by adGenAOSXConnectFirstIfType -- set to 0 if the interface can be defined by adGenAOSXConnectFirstIfNumber (and adGenAOSXConnectFirstSubIfNumber)

adGenAOSXConnectFirstTdmGroup.name: adGenAOSXConnectFirstTdmGroup
adGenAOSXConnectFirstTdmGroup.description: A number uniquely identifying the TDM Group associated with the interface described by adGenAOSXConnectFirstIfType -- set to 0 if it is not necessary that a TDM Group be associated with the interface

adGenAOSXConnectFirstTdmGroupDS0.name: adGenAOSXConnectFirstTdmGroupDS0
adGenAOSXConnectFirstTdmGroupDS0.description: The specific DS0 of the TDM Group, described by adGenAOSXConnectFirstTdmGroup, from which a cross- connect is being made -- set to 0 if it is not necessary that a specific timeslot be defined

adGenAOSXConnectSecondIfType.name: adGenAOSXConnectSecondIfType
adGenAOSXConnectSecondIfType.description: The type of interface to which a cross-connect is being made

adGenAOSXConnectSecondIfNumber.name: adGenAOSXConnectSecondIfNumber
adGenAOSXConnectSecondIfNumber.description: A number that defines the interface described by adGenAOSXConnectSecondIfType -- set to 0 if the interface can be defined by adGenAOSXConnectSecondIfSlot and adGenAOSXConnectSecondIfPort

adGenAOSXConnectSecondSubIfNumber.name: adGenAOSXConnectSecondSubIfNumber
adGenAOSXConnectSecondSubIfNumber.description: A number that further defines some interfaces -- set to 0 if the interface can be defined by adGenAOSXConnectSecondIfSlot and adGenAOSXConnectSecondIfPort

adGenAOSXConnectSecondIfSlot.name: adGenAOSXConnectSecondIfSlot
adGenAOSXConnectSecondIfSlot.description: The slot number containing the interface described by adGenAOSXConnectSecondIfType -- set to 0 if the interface can be defined by adGenAOSXConnectSecondIfNumber (and adGenAOSXConnectSecondSubIfNumber) Note: 0 is also a valid slot number.

adGenAOSXConnectSecondIfPort.name: adGenAOSXConnectSecondIfPort
adGenAOSXConnectSecondIfPort.description: The port number of the interface described by adGenAOSXConnectSecondIfType -- set to 0 if the interface can be defined by adGenAOSXConnectSecondIfNumber (and adGenAOSXConnectSecondSubIfNumber)

adGenAOSXConnectSecondTdmGroup.name: adGenAOSXConnectSecondTdmGroup
adGenAOSXConnectSecondTdmGroup.description: A number uniquely identifying the TDM Group associated with the interface described by adGenAOSXConnectSecondIfType -- set to 0 if it is not necessary that a TDM Group be associated with the interface

adGenAOSXConnectSecondTdmGroupDS0.name: adGenAOSXConnectSecondTdmGroupDS0
adGenAOSXConnectSecondTdmGroupDS0.description: The specific DS0 of the TDM Group, described by adGenAOSXConnectSecondTdmGroup, to which a cross- connect is being made -- set to 0 if it is not necessary that a specific timeslot be defined

adGenAOSXConnectPreserveRbs.name: adGenAOSXConnectPreserveRbs
adGenAOSXConnectPreserveRbs.description: The ability of the cross-connect to maintain robbed-bit signaling integrity -- set to disabled if robbed-bit signaling is not a characteristic of the cross-connect.

adGenAOSXConnectRowStatus.name: adGenAOSXConnectRowStatus
adGenAOSXConnectRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. Until instances of appropriate corresponding columns are configured, the value of the corresponding instance of the adGenAOSXConnectStatus column is 'notReady'.

adGenAOSTdmGroupTable.name: adGenAOSTdmGroupTable
adGenAOSTdmGroupTable.description: The TDM Group Table that associates DS0s into mappable units

adGenAOSTdmGroupEntry.name: adGenAOSTdmGroupEntry
adGenAOSTdmGroupEntry.description: An entry in the TDM Group Table

adGenAOSTdmGroupIfSlot.name: adGenAOSTdmGroupIfSlot
adGenAOSTdmGroupIfSlot.description: The slot number containing the interface for the TDM Group

adGenAOSTdmGroupIfPort.name: adGenAOSTdmGroupIfPort
adGenAOSTdmGroupIfPort.description: The port number containing the interface for the TDM Group

adGenAOSTdmGroupID.name: adGenAOSTdmGroupID
adGenAOSTdmGroupID.description: A number that uniquely defines the TDM Group

adGenAOSTdmGroupMask.name: adGenAOSTdmGroupMask
adGenAOSTdmGroupMask.description: A bitmap of the contiguous DS0s included in this TDM Group Example: mapping DS0s 1-12: 00000000000000000000111111111111 (bin), 00000FFF (hex), 4095 (dec) Note: To create a new row in adGenAOSTdmGroupTable, set adGenAOSTdmGroupMask with the appropriate index values corresponding to the desired slot, port, and TDM group ID

adGenAOSTdmGroupUsage.name: adGenAOSTdmGroupUsage
adGenAOSTdmGroupUsage.description: The speed of the individual DS0s

adGenAOSMuxConformancemModule.name: adGenAOSMuxConformancemModule
adGenAOSMuxConformancemModule.description: The compliance statement for SNMPv2 entities which implement the adGenAOSMux MIB.
